quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  86,1,"By the heaven, and the night-visitor,"
  86,2,"what do you know what the night-visitor is?"
  86,3,"It is the piercing star."
  86,4,"There is no living being but there is a protector over it."{1},footnotes:1:1
  86,5,"So let man consider of what he was created."{1},footnotes:1:1
  86,6,"He was created of a gushing fluid,"
  86,7,"emanating from between the loins and the ribs."{1},footnotes:1:1
  86,8,"Surely He (the Creator) has the power to bring him back (to life)."{1},footnotes:1:1
  86,9,"On the Day when man's deepest secrets shall be put to the test"{1},footnotes:1:1
  86,10,"he shall have no power, and no helper."
  87,1,"Glorify the name of your Lord, the Most High,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  87,2,"Who created all things and fashioned them in good proportion;"{1},footnotes:1:1
  87,3,"Who determined and guided them,"{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  87,4,"Who brought forth the pasture,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  87,5,"and then made it into a blackish straw."{1},footnotes:1:1
  87,6,"We shall make you recite and then you will not forget,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  87,7,"except what Allah should wish. He knows all that is manifest and all that is hidden."{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  87,8,"We shall ease you to follow the way of Ease."
  87,9,"So render good counsel if good counsel will avail."{1},footnotes:1:1
  87,10,"He who fears (Allah) shall heed it,"{1},footnotes:1:1